<HEAD>Man With Cane Beats Store Clerk, Takes Cash From Till</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAFAYETTE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A limping man used his cane to beat a
convenience store clerk and stole cash from the register after he
was told the liquor he wanted was available only in pints, police
said.
   The man limped off with $70 to $80, said police spokesman Ned
Ewing.
   The man, described as in his 30s, asked to buy a fifth of liquor
Friday and ``got agitated'' when told the store stocked what he
wanted only in the smaller size, Ewing said.
   The man beat the clerk on the head with his cane, then hit her
with a beer bottle, Ewing said. The clerk, who had been alone in the
store, ran into the bathroom screaming for help, he said.
   The man then rifled the cash register. A customer who entered the
store when the thief walked out found the clerk and called police.
