<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Massage     03-04 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Massage,0156</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chinese County Shuts Down Prostitution-Linked Massage Parlors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities in Baoan County have shut down all 16
of the area's massage parlors because of links to prostitution, an
official daily said Saturday.
   Baoan is the latest of several places in Guangdong province and
other areas of prosperous southern China to move against massage
parlors offering illicit sex to newly rich Chinese and visitors from
nearby Hong Kong.
   The overseas edition of the People's Daily said the county began
closing the parlors and removing their shop signs Jan. 21. The women
working in the shops, many of them recruited from rural areas
outside Guangdong, were sent home.
   The daily said massage parlors in Huidong County, to the east of
Baoan, are also being closed.
   Prostitution, virtually wiped out by the Communist government
after 1949, has made a comeback with the loosening of social and
economic controls in recent years.
</TEXT>
