<FIRST>r i AM-Bangladesh-Ferry     03-04 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bangladesh-Ferry,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ferry Capsizes, 23 Reported Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crowded ferry capsized Saturday in
southern Bangladesh, and at least 23 people drowned and many others
were missing, news reports said.
   Three bodies were recovered from the hull of the ferry after
rescue teams hauled the boat out of the swift flowing currents of
the Kancha river, United News of Bangladesh said.
   The other 20 bodies were found during a search of the accident
site, UNB said.
   The accident occurred near Hularhat, a town 85 miles south of
Dhaka.
   The ferry was designed to carry 85 people but actually carried
200 people and 26,400 pounds of rice, authorities told the news
agency. The weight caused the ferry to lose balance and overturn in
the river.
   The news agency said some people were missing, but it did not
give a specific figure.
   It said rescue operations were hampered by swift currents.
</TEXT>
