<HEAD>With AM-Eastern, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of major airline strikes from 1970 to present,
including the airline, when the strike began, the workers who began
the strike and the duration. The federal government deregulated the
airline industry in 1978.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>PRE-DEREGULATION</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   National Airlines, January 1970, general employees, 187 days
   Northwest Airlines, July 1970, clerks, 160 days
   Mohawk Airlines, November 1970, pilots, 154 days
   Hughes Air West, December 1971, mechanics, 118 days
   Northwest, June 1972, pilots, 95 days
   Ozark Airlines, April 1973, mechanics, 73 days
   Trans World Airlines, November 1973, flight attendants, 44 days
   National Airlines, July 1974, machinists, 110 days
   Texas International, December 1974, clerks, 125 days
   Air Lift International, November 1975, pilots, 109 days
   United Airlines, December 1975, machinists, 16 days
   Alaska Airlines, September 1976, flight attendants, 24 days
   Continental Airlines, October 1976, pilots, 24 days
   Wien Air Alaska, May 1977, pilots, more than one year
   Northwest, April 1978, pilots, 109 days
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>POST-DEREGULATION</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   United, March 1979, machinists, 58 days
   World Airways, August 1979, transport workers, 132 days
   Hughes Air West, September 1979, general employees, 61 days
   Ozark, September 1979, flight attendants, 52 days
   Southwest Airlines, January 1980, machinists, 19 days
   Ozark, May 1980, machinists, 27 days
   Pacific Southwest Airlines, September 1980, pilots, 52 days
   Continental, December 1980, flight attendants, 16 days
   Northwest, May 1982, mechanics, 34 days
   Continental, August 1983, machinists, never resolved
   Continental, October 1983, pilots, two years
   Pan Am, February 1985, transport workers, 47 days
   Alaska Airlines, March 1985, machinists, 59 days
   United, May 1985, pilots, 29 days
   TWA, March 1986, flight attendants, 64 days
   
   Sources: Mark L. Kahn, Airline Economics Inc.
