<FIRST>r a AM-Eastern-MachinistsDuties     03-04 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Eastern-Machinists Duties,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Machinists Union Divided Into Two Main Categories</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Eastern, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 8,500 members of the International Association
of Machinists at Eastern Airlines are divided about equally into two
categories: aircraft mechanics and ramp service workers.
   The mechanics at Eastern earn a top wage of $18.83 an hour,
compared with $16 to $20.10 an hour at other major U.S. airlines,
according to the union.
   The ramp service workers, who fuel planes, handle baggage and
drive motorized equipment on airport runways, make top pay of $15.60
an hour. That compares with $15.51 to $17.45 an hour at Eastern's
big competitors.
   The average age of Eastern Machinists is 38 to 39 years.
   The union members are predominantly male: 92 percent of the
mechanics and 86 percent of the ramp workers are men, the union says.
</TEXT>
