<FIRST>r i AM-ArianeLaunch     03-04 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Ariane Launch,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>European Rocket Launch Scrubbed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KOUROU, French Guiana (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 29th launch of Europe's Ariane
rocket was canceled three hours before lift-off Saturday night after
two cables were accidentally disconnected, officials said.
   The cables were pulled loose when the support tower was being
removed from the side of the launcher, said Frederic d'Allest,
president of Arianespace, which commercializes the rocket.
   It was not immediately clear whether the rocket could be launched
on Sunday night.
   It was the second launch postponement for the Ariane 4 rocket,
which was originally scheduled for lift-off on Tuesday but was
delayed by a strike at the launch base here.
   The cables that were accidentally detached served to ventilate
the MOP-1 European weather satellite, one of two payloads, and purge
oxygen reservoirs.
