weather an economic crisis that sparked nationwide riots and the
deaths this week of at least 300 people.
   President Carlos Andres Perez on Friday linked the bloodiest
civil unrest in Venezuela's history to the burden of its foreign
debt. He said debt payments threaten the newest democracies in Latin
America.
